				<li id="16690828" class="cmnt-root" data="37" data-d="1653025221000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578184/Carian-Knight's-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">20 May 2022 01:40</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16690828" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I think people maybe aren&apos;t using this sword in an effective way and mistake it as subpar. It&apos;s a great weapon. The AR is good, the AoW is amazing to use -- at the right times. Lots of veteran souls players tend to dismiss new mechanics that encourage more diverse gameplay like guard counters, blocking, stance breaking, etc. This weapon really shines when used with these new mechanics. <br/><br/>To anyone who finds themselves underwhelmed by the Carian Knight&apos;s Sword, I say give it another chance. Use a shield, use guard counters to break stances, then charge up the AoW. Even charging to the second stage is worth it. If you have high intelligence, it&apos;ll hit harder than a critical hit during a stance break.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16690828" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16690828" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">7</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><se