				<li id="16669903" class="cmnt-root" data="14" data-d="1651781562000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="https://fextralife.com/avatars/145980_1649238254.png" alt="" /><a class="comment-username" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&u=145980" rel="nofollow"  target="_blank" style="color: #;">LordAss777</a></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578184/Carian-Knight's-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">05 May 2022 16:12</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16669903" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">40 vigor, 99 endurance, 21 strength and dex, 18 int.<br/><br/>Does a neat 472 at +8, not the most viable way to play but the reason for that 99 endurance is because that charge r2 is block, practically hyperpoise you can treat it like it&apos;s hyperarmor.<br/><br/>I found out that playing with the highest permenant stamina of 211 is pretty fun, get to really play with the guard counters and with the carian knights sword, you get to play with the charge r2, because it&apos;s a block and the sword only has a gb of 31, you can&apos;t really utilize it against enemies with high poster damage but with 211 stamina oh boy you can enjoy the flavor of the r2.<br/><br/>Planning on doing pvp with this gemick build because I could probably catch people off guard with the r2 because they wouldn&apos;t expect someone with 211 stamina in the meta pvp lvl range, wouldn&apos;t win but like there is no point in taking pvp seriously.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16669903" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16669903" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>19</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>5</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16669903"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16669903" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16669903"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
				<li id="16668057" class="cmnt-root" data="57" data-d="1651664957000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578184/Carian-Knight's-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">04 May 2022 07:49</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16668057" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">CKS WS+Magic Scorpion Charm+Shard of Alexander+Godfrey Icon+Magic-Shrouding Cracked Tear=Excalibur Weapon Skill.<br/>Hits for 4376 when fully charged at 80 INT on the Wandering Nobles in Raya Lucaria Academy, and for 2917 on Malenia. You can bump that up with Stealth+Terra Magica for a total 7089 damage on the WN and 3938 on Malenia (minus stealth), although it&apos;s difficult to remain in the circle in most fights.<br/><br/>Excalibur WS+Altered Carian Knight Armor+Banished Knight Gauntlets+Cuckoo Knight Greaves+Bun Hairstyle=Decent Saber Cosplay. <br/>Consider adding the Altered Commoner&apos;s Headband to avoid nakedness (while preserving the bun hairstyle visible, which is nigh perfect with the tragic exception, of course, of the missing ahoge) and trying on the Banished Knight Greaves instead (I can&apos;t stand the duck-looking shoes, personally), to increase poise and damage absorption. Good options for the remaining talisman slot are Ritual Sword Talisman or Red-Feathered Branchsword (to squeeze more damage out of the WS if you want to play around with your HP), Dragoncrest Greatshield Talisman, Crimson Amber Medallion or Blessed Dew Talisman (for that Saber tankiness) or Bull-Goat&apos;s Talisman to help alleviate the issue of being interrupted mid swing.<br/><br/>As a nice touch I noticed, high INT (and some Mind) investment mimics Saber&apos;s mighty Magical Energy, Magical resistance, and of course, Noble Phantasm stats. Don&apos;t forget to yell &quot;EKUSU... KARIBA!&quot; when finishing off an enemy with Excalibur for maximum dopamine release.<br/><br/>As an aside, this weapon&apos;s WS is not the ultimate iteration of the Excalibur WS proper: if you&apos;re willing to sacrifice the beautiful looks of this sword and upgrade to the greatsword tier, a Magical Claymore with the Carian Grandeur AoW beats it in terms of raw damage with 3184 damage on Malenia with the same set up (4298 with Terra Magica), plus it deals way more posture damage, being able to open Malenia for a riposte on two consecutive swings (CKS&apos;s WS didn&apos;t do it even after three), which are extremely easy to land given she&apos;s so passive and the first swing will knock her to the ground. Dragons and creatures that take extra damage to the head will also be open for a critical after the second consecutive fully charged hit, and most humanoid enemies will be knocked down after even an uncharged hit, allowing you to chain them (this last part applies to CKS&apos;s WS too). I also went through the trouble of verifying if it did more damage when applied to a different sword (it didn&apos;t on Lordsworn&apos;s Greatsword), whether it was viable with a Cold Infusion instead (probably, AoW WS does less damage but still does slightly more than CKS WS, and you have to factor in Frozen status effect and the extra damage derived from it. WS does not build up frost, however) and whether going all the way up to 99 INT was worth it (not really, biggest damage difference I could note was about 100 on Malenia when inside Terra Magica).<br/><br/>A couple other points of interest: Carian Grandeur (both CKS and the AoW version) appears to scale solely with INT, which is why I didn&apos;t bother mentioning the Strength or Dex stats, but you should pay attention to those if you&apos;re trying to make a build that doesn&apos;t lean entirely on the WS. That also means it&apos;s not affected by purely physical damage modifiers, and it probably explains why the AoW version does more damage than the CKS WS: an infused magical weapon has better INT scaling, which is somewhat funny and tragic. It does the same damage all across the swing, unlike DS3&apos;s Dragonslayer Axe WA that did more damage if the weapon connected. It also does way more damage than backstabs if you&apos;re sneaking up on enemies, and even crits if you get a chance to riposte them.<br/><br/>As part of the challenge of trying to make the WS shine, I beat the game by spamming it non-stop against everything I came across and was pleasantly surprised by how viable it became after the latest patch (and a bit of finnessing with the talisman set up): it bodies most humanoids, destroys several bosses (including Malenia), and kicks ass all around, due in no small part to Elden Ring&apos;s enemies&apos; tendency to having long wind ups before attacking and it&apos;s impressive range that can allow you to hit from relative safety, although it is tragically weak against big enemies that spam fast attacks like the giant birds in Caelid that can prevent you from getting a hit in entirely.<br/><br/>A closing remark regarding the issue of poise/hyperarmor I see thrown around often: it&apos;s not nearly as bad as you might think. It&apos;s bad! But not nearly as bad. Building up to 30ish poise and throwing on the Poise talisman will allow you to resist up to a couple of small hits (like a dog&apos;s) without getting interrupted, and a single one from medium sized enemies and bosses (like Malenia or The Godskin fellas), although it&apos;ll still get interrupted by big enemies and bosses (like the bears or dragons). Alternatively, really heavy armor can make you capable of resisting even some big hits without getting interrupted. The biggest issue I&apos;ve found with getting hit mid swing, funnily enough, appears to be a glitch: a lot of the time your character manages to resist the attack and continue the animation, but has their aim modified slightly, resulting in them hitting NEXT to the enemy and missing them, which is horrifically frustrating since it leaves you vulnerable and has no chance of trading, which just means wasted HP&amp;FP and potential death. This seems to happen mostly with fully charged hits while getting hit by medium sized enemies, and it still has a chance to connect if they&apos;re close enough their hit box is still in the way. The only way I found to deal with this is not locking on and instead free aiming the attack, which stops it from having its trajectory changed.<br/><br/>If that issue were to be fixed and/or the hyperarmor/poise was improved, this wouldn&apos;t just be my favorite Weapon Skill in the game, it might legitimately be one of the best. As it stands, however, it&apos;s still really solid, and most of all, incredibly fun to use.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16668057" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16668057" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">9</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>66</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>9</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16668057"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16668057" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16668057"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
