				<li id="16646368" class="cmnt-root" data="1" data-d="1650948095000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578184/Carian-Knight's-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">26 Apr 2022 00:41</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16646368" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I don&apos;t think this sword is super bad, I think people just want it to be something other than what it is just because it looks nice. It has pretty decent base damage, low requirements, and though the AoW is not unique, it hits hard and is not difficult to land when used judiciously (so long as you don&apos;t get greedy with the charges). You can get some additional gains on the weapon art with Godfrey&apos;s Icon &amp; Alexander&apos;s Shard, but even without those upgrades it&apos;s pretty good. The guarding R2 is interesting, but IMO too niche with too little damage reduction to be a selling feature.<br/><br/>The scaling ain&apos;t gonna make anyone get up and sing, but IMO the base damage makes this a respectable sidearm for a mage character focused primarily on INT. If you want a straight sword with better INT scaling, the regular ol&apos; Longsword with Magic Affinity looks like it has B scaling on INT. Or you could go for a true hybrid build and just use enchantment spells with whatever dex/str sword you like with a Keen/Heavy/Quality Affinity.<br/></p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16646368" class="c