				<li id="16592320" class="cmnt-root" data="9" data-d="1649125422000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578184/Carian-Knight's-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">04 Apr 2022 22:23</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16592320" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">This weapon, while it was poorly implemented, is a bit underrated in terms of PvP ability. <br/><br/>The weapon itself does decent damage for a straight sword, and it looks pretty stylish too. It’s ability to trade, while it is nowhere near as good as Valorheart’s, is still respectable. It’s WA is also pretty bad for PvP.<br/><br/>At 36 End and with the Greatshield Talisman, I was able to trade with most weapons. The strongest attack it can survive is the r1 of the greatsword. <br/><br/>When dueling against moonveil users, i recommend applying as much pressure as possible in order to prevent them from using their WA. You should also utilize sorceries such as star shower and swift glinstone shard in order to prevent them from spamming stars or ruin.<br/><br/>For RoB users, I also recommend applying a lot of pressure. Unfortunately, opponents with high poise will be able to tank most of your attacks. If you’re opponent is at low health, and you have HP to spare, then you may be able to trade the first combo of the WA.<br/><br/>For vyke’s spear, you can trade most of their attacks. For the WA, if your madness bar is not 25% or more filled, you can roll into the blast and go for a backstab.<br/><br/>For opponents using colossal weapons, try to utilize their slow attack speed to your advantage. Do not attempt to trade.<br/><br/>When playing against powerstanced bleed builds, great swords, and halberds, do not attempt to trade.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16592320" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16592320" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>10</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>1</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16592320"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16592320" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16592320"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
