				<li id="16531131" class="cmnt-root" data="48" data-d="1647598945000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578184/Carian-Knight's-Sword" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">18 Mar 2022 06:22</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16531131" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Why does a magic sword scale better with strength than it does with intelligence? The crystal sword does too and it makes me seethe. I get hybrid builds, I really do, but they couldn&apos;t have just given it decent INT scaling? Especially on the best looking straight sword in the game (in my opinion) and they do us dirty with the D INT scaling. Amazing. Moonveil +9 with 60 INT does like 730AR with a freakin light attack due to the high dex requirement and the high INT scaling, and it gets an extremely quick to deploy and powerful weapon art. I think they should improve the scaling or at least just make it able to be infused so you can at least put a useable weapon art on there. Good luck getting someone to let you stand there for 5 seconds in PvP while you charge up your super-slicer. Some dork with a Moonveil is just going to hit you with the heavy weapon art every time you try and charge yours up.<br/><br/>I don&apos;t even hate Moonveil, it&apos;s extremely easy to dodge 1v1 and is great for PvE. It also looks really good imo. I just hate how bows and a lot of other weapons get the short end of the stick. Moonveil is fine, everything else just sucks lol.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed">